content:
A census provides a statistical snapshot of the eligible members of a group (for example, employees) and their legal dependents. You can use a census for group benefits quoting and rating as well as the subsequent enrollment process.

Vlocity Insurance has a deep set of features to manage and upload censuses for small and large group insurance plans.

The Census object (GroupCensus__c) provides a snapshot of statistics about members of a group and their legal dependents. The Census Member object (GroupCensusMember__c) represents specific personal information about a member or a dependent.

The Census object has two Record Types, for Small Group and Large Group plans, which are based on the number of employees enrolled in a plan.

The Census object's Type field defines the census under one of the following categories: System, Quote, or Enrollment. A System census maintains active membership; Quote is attached to a quote and locked down from edits; and Enrollment defines members offered enrollment and their dependents.

All employees and their dependents have census member records, which form family groups with the employee as primary member. The Census Member object has fields for first name, last name, and concatenated name.

The Census object also has roll-up summary fields to count family tiers and other employee and family numbers.

You can use the InsCensusService: convertLeadAndCreateCensus service in an OmniScript to create Census records from Leads.

After adding a Group, you're ready to upload group benefits census data for the group members using census records.
title: Vlocity Insurance Group Benefits Census
